<para id="para-00001">Four primary types of <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00001">microorganisms</term> are responsible for causing infections in humans: bacteria, viruses, fungi, and parasites. This chapter will introduce the various pharmacologic agents designed to treat infections caused by these microorganisms, including indications, mechanisms, adverse effects, contraindications, and drug interactions.</para>
